   "source": [
    "# Filtre de Kalman - Théorie et Simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "## Théorie\n",
    "\n",
    "Le système linéaire à temps discret est défini par les équations suivantes :\n",
    "\n",
    "$$X_{n+1} = F X_n + T_{n+1},$$\n",
    "$$Y_{n+1} = G X_{n+1} + U_{n+1},$$\n",
    "\n",
    "où $T_{n+1} \sim \mathcal{N}(0,Q)$ et $U_{n+1} \sim \mathcal{N}(0,R)$ sont des bruits gaussiens, et $F$ et $G$ sont les matrices de transition et d'observation respectivement.\n",
    "\n",
    "Le filtre de Kalman est composé des étapes de prédiction et de mise à jour :\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prédiction :**\n",
    "$$\hat{X}_{n+1|n} = F \hat{X}_{n|n}, \quad P_{n+1|n} = F P_{n|n} F^\top + Q$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mise à jour :**\n",
    "$$K_{n+1} = P_{n+1|n} G^\top (G P_{n+1|n} G^\top + R)^{-1}$$\n",
    "$$\hat{X}_{n+1|n+1} = \hat{X}_{n+1|n} + K_{n+1}(Y_{n+1} - G \hat{X}_{n+1|n})$$\n",
    "$$P_{n+1|n+1} = (I - K_{n+1} G) P_{n+1|n}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Paramètres du modèle\n",
    "F = np.array([[0.9]])\n",
    "G = np.array([[1.0]])\n",
    "Q = np.array([[0.1]])\n",
    "R = np.array([[0.5]])\n",
    "N = 50\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialisation\n",
    "X = np.zeros((1, N+1))\n",
    "Y = np.zeros((1, N+1))\n",
    "X_hat = np.zeros((1, N+1))\n",
    "P = np.zeros((1, 1, N+1))\n",
    "X[:,0] = 0.0\n",
    "P[:,:,0] = 1.0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulation des données\n",
    "for n in range(N):\n",
    "    T = np.random.multivariate_normal(mean=[0], cov=Q)\n",
    "    U = np.random.multivariate_normal(mean=[0], cov=R)\n",
    "    X[:,n+1] = F @ X[:,n] + T\n",
    "    Y[:,n+1] = G @ X[:,n+1] + U\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtre de Kalman\n",
    "for n in range(N):\n",
    "    X_pred = F @ X_hat[:,n]\n",
    "    P_pred = F @ P[:,:,n] @ F.T + Q\n",
    "    K = P_pred @ G.T @ np.linalg.inv(G @ P_pred @ G.T + R)\n",
    "    X_hat[:,n+1] = X_pred + K @ (Y[:,n+1] - G @ X_pred)\n",
    "    P[:,:,n+1] = (np.eye(1) - K @ G) @ P_pred\n",
    "\n",
    "# Affichage\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "plt.plot(X.flatten(), label='État vrai')\n",
    "plt.plot(Y.flatten(), 'o', label='Observations', markersize=3)\n",
    "plt.plot(X_hat.flatten(), label='Estimation KF')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Pas de temps')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Valeur')\n",
    "plt.title('Filtre de Kalman sur système linéaire')\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
